name: r-mskcc.oncotree
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.1.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-mskcc.oncotree
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/mskcc.oncotree_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/mskcc.oncotree/mskcc.oncotree_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f79b0c1b6cfbdaf2c3ee70d12d9c0eb117021750a68816648b0e36c58b391c35

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-glue
    - r-httr2
    - r-magrittr
    - r-memoise
    - r-purrr
    - r-readr
    - r-rlang
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyjson
    - r-tidyr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-glue
    - r-httr2
    - r-magrittr
    - r-memoise
    - r-purrr
    - r-readr
    - r-rlang
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyjson
    - r-tidyr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('mskcc.oncotree')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('mskcc.oncotree')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://maialab.org/mskcc.oncotree/
  license: MIT
  summary: Programmatic access to 'OncoTree' API <http://oncotree.mskcc.org/>. Get access to
    tumor main types, identifiers and utility routines to map across to other tumor
    classification systems.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
